The modern approach uses Flexbox:
```css
.parent {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
}
```
Or with Grid:
```css
.parent {
  display: grid;
  place-items: center;
}
```

For a known-width element, use absolute positioning:
```css
.child {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
}
```
For inline/inline-block elements, use `text-align: center` on the parent and `vertical-align: middle`.

